== Basic Definition ==


Vicarious Reinforcement is defined in "''Psychology for AS Level 3rd Edition''" by ''Michael W. Eysenck'' as being reinforcement gained by watching another person.

----


== Example in Context ==


An example of this would be If person A was to watch person B put his hand into a bucket of boiling water and then remove his hand from the bucket with burn marks, peeling skin and noticable pain, Person A would learn from watching this that to put their own hand in a bucket of boiling water is bad. Thus they have recieved reinforcement from another person.

----


== Used in... ==


Vicarious Reinforcement is often used as a key work in the Social Learning Theory in the area of Developmental Psychology